comment.body:
@Krixano: You do have a point about the usability. And some people who want to start projects may lack the knowledge to clone and edit the zite (something I didn't think about earlier). 
What I meant by making something cloneable per project, is that you would allow a person to freely change it to fit the project that person is working on. Like you said. It would allow for the introduction of new features for example by a bigger audience, however this bigger audience can still clone your central zite and add some features. (I think I was over-reacting hehe.) 
But if that would happen, we would be competing with each other, which would be kind of unnecessary. Merger zites would probably deal with this, right? Merger zites would basically allow access to the same data through different zites with different features. Would be great if it could work like this.
